      "plot": "The Tramp cares for an abandoned child, but events put their relationship in jeopardy. The opening title reads: \"A comedy with a smile A woman decides to abandon her baby in the backseat of an automobile with a handwritten note attached, beseeching the finder to care for and love the child. When thieves steal the car and discover the baby in the backseat, they leave him on the street and he's discovered by the initially-reluctant Tramp, who eventually softens and comes to love him as his own. As the boy grows up, both he and The Tramp must learn to navigate through a life that spawns one adventure after another.Perez The unwed Mother  leaves a charity hospital with her newborn, disconsolately passes a church wedding, and leaves her baby in a limousine with a note. But car thieves steal the limo and dump the baby in the garbage, where he is discovered by a Tramp . The Tramp rescues the infant and takes him to raise. Five years later, the Mother has become an opera star and does charity work hoping to relocate her son. The Tramp has raised the Kid to work a scam in tandem: the boy breaks windows by tossing rocks, and the Tramp shows up instantly and offers to repair them for a fee. A doctor tips off the Mother, who has the authorities pick up the child, but the Tramp steals him back and a chase ensues. This was Chaplin's first six-reel feature; he had to hold it hostage to get the studio to pay him the $1.5 million he was entitled to when they tried to pay him for only a two-reeler. A 12-year-old girl named Lillita McMurray appears briefly in the film as a flirtatious angel; three years later she would become pregnant by the writer-director and marry him at age 16.",
