      "plot": "While trying to leave a quiet suburban life, a family of undercover superheroes are forced into action to save the world. Bob Parr , and his wife Helen , are the world's greatest famous crime In this lauded Pixar animated film, married superheroes Mr. Incredible and Elastigirl are forced to assume mundane lives as Bob and Helen Parr after all super-powered activities have been banned by the government. While Mr. Incredible loves his wife and kids, he longs to return to a life of adventure, and he gets a chance when summoned to an island to battle an out-of-control robot. Soon, Mr. Incredible is in trouble and it's up to his family to save him.Who would have thought that the world, and, especially, the good people of Metroville would have enough of masked crime fighters and super-heroes? Now, fifteen long years, and several lawsuits later, the once-popular super-strong defender, Bob Parr, aka \"Mr Incredible\", and his exceptional elastomer-limbed wife, Helen, aka \"Elastigirl\", find themselves living an ordinary suburban life as civilians with their equally extraordinary three kids. But suddenly, a mysterious invitation jolts Bob into action, and for the first time in a long while, Mr Parr feels useful, doing what he does best--behind Helen's back, of course. Once more, the Earth is in danger. Can the long-forgotten Incredibles save the day?Riganas Superheroes are no longer a secret to the world; their identities are known to the US Government and they've become model citizens in a conforming world. But heroes know no limits to persistence. Retired superhero Mr. Incredible receives a mysterious message from a mysterious woman on a seemingly deserted island. Little does Mr. Incredible realize that he'll soon be in the cross-hairs of a conspiracy involving all the world's superheroes.Mr. Incredible is a superhero; or he used to be, until a surge of lawsuits against superheroes submitted by the people they've saved forced the government to hide them in witness protection programs so they could lead normal, anonymous lives. Now known exclusively by his secret identity, Bob Parr, he lives with his wife Helen, formerly Elastigirl, and their three children Violet, Dash, and Jack-Jack. He works as an insurance-claims specialist, and he's fed up with his pushy boss and his immoral profession, but his wife's worked too hard to build a normal life for her family to abide his nostalgia for heroism. When Mr. Incredible's offered the chance to play the role of hero again by a mysterious informant, he jumps at the opportunity, and the whole family must reveal themselves to save Mr. Incredible and countless innocents.Loughrin",
